snippet.textDisplay:
"[...] Because it is very restrictive". I'm always a bit sad when I hear people say this. It's actually one of the least restrictive diets (apart from "omnivore-shove-it-all-down" of course). You can basically eat pretty much ANYTHING apart from meat, fish, dairy, eggs, honey.


The restriction most people see is actually when eating out and buying ready-to-go foods. It's our environment (restaurants, food industry, supermarkets, etc.) that needs to change and make it way more natural and accessible to actually eat healthy.

I'm finding it horrendous that we as consumers have to take such an insane amount of carefulness when choosing our groceries because most stuff that's not pure veggies, fruits, nuts, etc. is 90% just crap. Trying to sell useless calories to an already overeaten but undernourished society and make us all more sick and obese altogether.

There's more than enough evidence that suggests that our environment plays a vital role in our habits. i.e. if you rarely get the chance to eat chocolate and other crap because it's just not really accessible, you won't consume it that much. Same goes for meat, etc.
But as long as every restaurant and every person defaults to "meat is a good main dish" nothing's gonna ever change.
